Ok guys this is going to be a long headcanon about david because Ive been thinking about it for a while now  So what if David is kind of like max in the sense that he never really had supporting parents that were there for him either In this episode he acts angry when Max is clearly starting to get upset about the fact his parents dont care about him Now we could all write that off as David just being normal oblivious David but hear me out As we know from before David has either ptsd that has illusioned him into thinking that his friend jasper survived or he at least wants to remember it that way As we saw when he was a kid David acted a LOT like Max does regarding how he thinks of the camp and the people If Davids friend really did die that day its not unlikely that he might have blamed himself for it and took a completely different direction in how he thought of the camp wanting his friend to not have died in vain he decided that he would understand how amazing the camp is and even go on to become its leader If his parents were like Maxs they probably wouldnt have cared what happened to him anyway So he became a camp counseler to always have something to remind him of what happened because of him since he may think that jaspers death was his fault so he never would act that way again Hence becoming incredibly happy and wanting to have an amazing outlook on life So when Max kept on acting like he did it infuriated David not because of Max being angry but because he saw himself in Max and hated the fact he used to be that way This may not have only been an episode about healing Max but also about David starting to fix his past wounds by helping Max and seeing what seems to be a younger version of himself if his friend hadnt died Idk i mean its just headcanon but it just seems like something more serious is going on in this show Thanks for anyone who read this whole thing Sorry for it being so long XD

Oscar is Ozpin in the past Im calling it heres why
A they look alike Hair style eye color lean body type freckles go away with age and the tan can be from the fact that Oscar is a farmer Definitely possible that Ozpin loses his tan from being away from the farm
B I have a theory that Ozpins semblance is something to do with time I think alot of ppl have that same theory what with all the clock gear imagery in his tower and the fact that in his fight against cinder he was so unbelievable fast perhaps he was slowing time then doing his strikes
C IF his semblance really is time I think that he would send messages back in time to himself to warn him of what will happen in the future that way hed have time to prepare for it better Which can explain why Ozpin is so smart calculating and seemingly all knowing in the present that weve seen him in It would also explain why Ozpin was able to talk to Oscar and why Oscar looked in the mirror and was touching his hair perhaps confused at the fact that it had changed color
D Oscar seems to be living in a time with very little to no technology I know its reasonable to say that on a farm one would lack technology to begin with but even on a farm you have tractors and some sort of water distribution system or a better way to get fresh water instead of using the pump behind his barn Even for a farm his farm is super void of any modern day technology and in comparison to the technology present in the remnant weve seen Oscars time is very very very far behind
E In the Wizard of Oz the Wizards first name is Oscar and its no surprise that Ozpin is based off the Wizard from the Wizard of Oz so are all of the other staff academic heads Also weve never been told of Ozpins first name we know he is Professor Ozpin but professors are referred to by last name so we have no clue what the first name is SO if we go by the theory that Ozpin is based off the Wizard in the Wizard of Oz which is pretty much a confirmed fact by roosterteeth at this point then its a very VERY fair assumption to make that his first name is Oscar and typically in shows you dont have more than one character with the same first name which leads me to believe that Oscar and Ozpin are the same So Overall

Plus they literally emit positive vibrations
Cats are the best medicine for everything

What I love with these is that I can identify them with my own cats  One night my father found a tiny kitten had been thrust in the hedge  He was five weeks old and his eyes were glued shut with cat flu  He was rushed into the vet  We named him Thomas  The next night we found his sister on the hedge  The third night I heard a kitten mewling outside but we couldnt find it  The poor little girl had chronic ill health she had to be put on valium and eventually she had to be put to sleep because she paralyzed her back and rear end  We were all crying because we loved and cared for her so dearly  But her brother was an energetic little cat who loved pouncing  on his little sister  So my father went to the local cat shelter and adopted another little girl who needed vet care because of a serious dose of gastroenteritis  She came home a two month old baby with serious diarrhea  So Thomas saw this little baby and thought I can push her around  We would hear a squeal shout Thomas leave her alone she is a baby and rush to see Thomas being thrown onto his back and this little baby scragging hell out of him  After two days Thomas was hiding and running from little Cindy  That is what the third cartoon reminded me of

When I was a kid we had a neighbor who moved away and was so irresponsible as to abandon five pregnant female cats We took them all in and they all delivered their litters within the same week We blocked off the largest room in the house and turned it over to the kittens for the most adorable chaos ever Our house was mostly an open plan house so we didnt have a door on the wide entrance to the den which was the largest room and instead blocked it off with a closet door that was taken off its hinges and laid on its side across the portal Well one particularly adventurous kitten whom I called Patches because he was white with gray spots learned how to get over that door and then taught the rest of them the trick So we got a sheet of plywood that was taller than the door had been wide They got over that So we got a new sheet of plywood that was so tall we had to cut a door into it like at an ice hockey rink and they still got over it Finally we topped it with plexiglass cementing the appearance of this room to a hockey rink and they couldnt get over that But they tried Patches was also the first to learn how to climb the curtains First he got halfway and then mewed until someone got him down Then he got all the way to the top of the curtain rod and mewed to be set down Then he walked to the other side of the curtain rod and mewed to be set down Then the most worrying thing happened he stopped mewing because hed discovered the secret of how to slide down the curtains with his claws out One day I came into the den and saw him leading a line of six other kittens across the curtain rod all of them to end their journey the same way by shredding the curtains We kept them for six months until they could be weaned had them all neutered and given a checkout and then gave all but six away from approximately two dozen after personally interviewing each prospect Then we got rid of the curtains the carpet and replaced all the furniture It was horrendously timeconsuming and expensive but Im proud of my parents for not just leaving the pregnant cats or turning them over to a shelter

I had a lot of outdoor barn cats in my life but until someone dumped a week old halfdead kitten at my door 9 years ago never an indoor cat  Sita brought me SO much in those 7 years even saving my life one day when I fell in my tub broke my hip  severed an artery  She actually brought me my toy an older iPod and I texted my daughter who called 911  2 years ago she died in a fire at my home  I was hospitalized for days from Smoke inhalation from trying to get to her firemen actually had to drag me out by my ankles    Sita used to sleep wrapped around mekind of spooning me from the front  And Heaven forbid if I didnt have HER pillow and HER blanket ready at bedtime A few weeks later a friend in town called and said someone had left a kitten probably a month or so old outside her storeand I took in my furry Leela I had never thought of cats as particularly loving but Leela is THE most loving critter Ive ever had She gives kisses jumps up  hugs me around my neck  especially if shes done something wrong and cuddles at nightnot QUITE as close as Sita didbut *I*m certainly sleeping better  Shes stolen my wedge Im supposed to sleep on and even during the dayits the ONLY place she sleeps  Oh and she whispers meow each morning gently tapping my cheekto let me know shes ready for breakfast    Ive also trained her better to come take her out for walks and have prepared everything in case God forbid theres another fire  I cant go through THAT again

If anyones interested in how claw machines are rigged heres some interesting factoids
Claw machines are designed to slowly grab tighter over a certain number of goes So say its set to a 30go cycle after 30 goes the claw will grab as tight as it ever grabs and this is usually when people win After that it will slowly get weaker before getting stronger again on another 30go cycle So if you can watch people play a claw machine for long enough you should be able to work out how long the cycle is based on when people win and then you can work out the best times to play to win Or you could actually enjoy your life and just play it straight away and if you dont win you dont win
